courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students are expected to be able to
• understand basic features of the German language;
• understand selected information related to German culture;
• identify “international” loanwords (e.g. “kindergarten”) as a helpful means to understand vocabulary;
• recognise the relationship between English and German in terms of vocabulary;
• apply basic structures to simple everyday situations, e.g. greetings, introducing oneself and others, expressing food preferences and dislikes, and talking about hobbies;
• implement independent learning as part of their learning experience.

Upon completion of the course, the student should be able to deal with a range of situations in German such as
• discussing one’s living situation;
• discussing holiday and vacation;
• reporting about Germany and one’s own country;
• talking about health and nutrition;
• talking about events of the past.
